22/02/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police searched nearly 190 homes and confiscated computers in a massive crackdown on paedophiles and child pornography.
The raids Thursday (February 21st) were part of an international operation organised by Interpol.
Police refused to reveal more details except that the "Sledgehammer" operation had been planned since September.
(HRT, HINA, Javno.com, Reuters - 21/02/08)
